	Joined: Mar 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>You know, Saar, there's a lot there for a non-raider.<br />
<br />
Solo Ldon style content.<br />
New Ldon loot above the 1492 level.<br />
Removable augmentations.<br />
Tradeable charms.<br />
Increased number of buff slots (PoK MGBfest + SK in group will get 15 now).<br />
More tradeskill content.<br />
<br />
But if you're committed to being done with the game, then nothing would really have changed your mind, I expect.  But although a lot of the flashy stuff was about raids (PoTime *needs* to be fixed, trust us on this one), there's more there for the "everyman" player than usual, too.  I give it a "cautiously optimistic" so far.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
