<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>SlimBritches</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: May 2004<br />
	Location: Inside 'dese SLIM BRITCHES! YOWZA!
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>The only craptastic part about it, imo, is that there aren't any real shaman specific things listed.<br />
<br />
I absolutely love the AA buff slot increase... it is my favorite item.  I am so tired of having to get people to leave a HoT slot open (Yeah, people still block it around me, with things as dumb as cobalt procs or ultravision or what not).<br />
<br />
I like the idea of solo-able missions with NPC helpers, though I know the coding would most likely be horrific.<br />
<br />
Think it's funny how Druids want a group heal and faster/more efficient heals, and the resistance check on ONE of their spells fixed.<br />
<br />
They should try rolling a shaman and PL'ing him up like crazy with their dr00d here in the GoD era, see how they like their heals and 0 resist modifier spells then!<br />
<br />
I'm soooooo soooooo glad to see a list of improvements that doesn't consist of 50 percent "We will fix collision."  The recent collision issues will most likely never be fully fixed, and at this point I'm not even hoping for much improvement... as it only bugs me when it happens to raid mobs (ugh)... but what I AM tired of is the collision being the focus of the last what, 5 or 6 patches?  Seems like it overshadows other things.<br />
<br />
The whole no drop thing does not effect us players on Firiona Vie, though I imagine it would help across the other servers.<br />
<br />
And I never expected them to instance Time... no matter how badly old zones need features from newer ones sometimes, instancing being the best example to date imo, they (SoE) usually just leave it alone.  I wish they were more specific on how they are taking steps towards instancing... I don't see how you can do it halfway, it's either instanced or not... but any changes to help allow more people to tackle it is VERY needed, as more and more guilds reach it and it is a pseudo-requirement for deep Gates Content, and, presumably, some Omens Content.<br />
<br />
I am incredibly sick of the Alien theme.  Planes of Power totally rocked, as it reinforced a lot of old storyline and you got to see some of the gods you always heard about, as well as beefed up versions of old plane ones (sure you end up helping to kill the gods you worship for progression now and then, but we'll just overlook that...)<br />
<br />
Gates is just stupid, it's like a B horror movie.  They went way too far with the new storyline... they took 5 years of Norrathian lore and threw it to the crapper in exchange for a story based upon some poorly evolved characters that, while posessing of potential, lack the support of any eloquent writers (the in-game story chapters are quite blandly written).<br />
<br />
I want to hear about Norrath, not about three fellas and a wacky mage.  Granted the story was fun at first, it is overshadowing the more awesome lore of previous expansions, my favorite of which was Velious (LOVED that lore, remember the three different letters from different travelers, all based on different factions, in the manual?  Sigh.... memories <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" />   )<br />
<br />
Very happy about backflagging solutions... perhaps they could do some easier versions of flagging that include requiring someone with the flags already on as a helper, that would go a long way.  <br />
<br />
Also glad they examining raid exp, with most high level characters simply logging on to raid and then off when an alt is played (because *gasp*, it's sorta fun to run around at a lower level doing whatcha want in old zones!!!), the necessity to break off and AA grind is kinda crappy, and we all now how insignificant raid exp is compared to grinding >:\</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />A good pair of slim britches reminds you that you're alive.  YOWZA!</div>
	
