	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Well, I guess I need to defend myself.  Maybe there are shaman specific things coming, let's hope so.  <br />
<br />
-potime fixes (not true instancing yet but a step -- i was told full instancing will take a bit longer due to having to make major changes)<br />
   + so what, I'm not in PoTime, maybe it's good for you, I'll take your word<br />
-raid message of the day<br />
   + a minor convenience, gonna make me wanna keep playing EQ? nah. <br />
-improving how soe handles beta and the testing process<br />
   + big f'ing deal<br />
-increasing the number of debuffs allowed on a mob<br />
   + sure, might be good, never ran into this problem myself<br />
-increase buffslots on players through aa<br />
   + great, so now my excuse for only doing Fo7 and Boar to save buff spots is gone; spot for heal over time is okay<br />
-note field on the raid window<br />
   + minor convenience, who cares<br />
-improved consent (/consent guild) and drag. /consent raid, guild, or group.<br />
   + minor convenience, big deal... rogue no longer gets spammed with consents, yay, i'm excited<br />
-improve corpse drag radius<br />
   + ????  big f'ing deal again<br />
-make charms not no drop<br />
   + big f'ing deal again<br />
<br />
The "longer to-do list" - again, not everything but this is what they'll be discussing immediately:<br />
<br />
-back flagging solutions<br />
   + /shrug<br />
-improved raid and guild functionality<br />
   + /shrug<br />
-auto loot for your corpse<br />
   + wow, something that could have been around since day one, want to bet how many /petitions they get because someone looted before res?<br />
-improvements to raid xp<br />
   + ok, yes, I like this one... raid xp sucks and my AA progress screeches to a halt when I raid.<br />
-no more alien NPC's (focussing more on familiar norrathian themes)<br />
   + I don't care<br />
-solo ldon-stle instanced or similar content<br />
   + this is only thing I can get excited about if done right, has great possibilities; I agree with previous poster that said that rewards from solo LDON's will be ridiculously expensive for the time and/or crappy<br />
-issues with item augmentations (also refers to focii/effects i believe)<br />
  + this one will also be good, as long as they also institute an LDON gear buyback<br />
-possible enhancements to /guildwar<br />
   + .... who cares<br />
<br />
<br />
Hope you all found some good things here.  If you found one thing that you think is half way decent and you consider it a success, then good for you.  Sounds to me like an incredible waste of time and money.<br />
<br />
Mach</p>
	
	
	
