	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Saar_Tribunal</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Mar 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Shabura Naarteban</b><br /><i>You know, Saar, there's a lot there for a non-raider.<br />
<br />
Solo Ldon style content.<br />
New Ldon loot above the 1492 level.<br />
Removable augmentations.<br />
Tradeable charms.<br />
Increased number of buff slots (PoK MGBfest + SK in group will get 15 now).<br />
More tradeskill content.<br />
<br />
But if you're committed to being done with the game, then nothing would really have changed your mind, I expect.  But although a lot of the flashy stuff was about raids (PoTime *needs* to be fixed, trust us on this one), there's more there for the "everyman" player than usual, too.  I give it a "cautiously optimistic" so far.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I dont get why raiders especially serious raiders seem to think LDoN is a panacea for the non-raider.<br />
<br />
Completely over looking the repetitiveness of it, the blandness, etc lets look at time investment.<br />
<br />
Approximately 5000 points per item (item plus augs)<br />
Approximately 100 adventures per item (51 points per adventure)<br />
Approximately 150-200 hours per item (1.5-2 hours per adventure)<br />
Multiply that by 10 items<br />
1500-2000 HOURS or LDoN time for those items<br />
Divide by 20 hours per week<br />
75-100 WEEKS<br />
Divide by 52 (weeks in a year)<br />
<br />
Final:<br />
1.5 - 2 YEARS of time for 10 pieces of gear.<br />
<br />
So they are adding higher priced items?<br />
Result: Longer to get that gear, now 3 years?<br />
<br />
So they are adding solo LDoN?<br />
Result: Less points per adventure, longer to get gear, again now 3 years?<br />
<br />
Increased buff slots? I think only raiders ever get full of usable buffs, I sure dont.<br />
<br />
Tradable charms? very minor, I have never even seen a decent charm.<br />
<br />
Removable augs? Not all that useful to ME as it would take me like 2 months for one item with augs, how long after that would I want to change those augs around? The people I hear complaining about augs are raiders who want to move their Anger3 augs to new raid drop weapons.<br />
<br />
No I dont see anything about improving PROGRESSION for the non-raider. Note the all caps word there. There is no where to go. LDoN for 6 months, then LDoN hards for 6 months, then GoD? I have pickup groups wipe in LDoN normals still. Most of the raiders dont have any idea how it is for people at this level of the game. I dont want RAID content, I want content just like I had for levels 1-65. At 65+ there is none.<br />
<br />
I'm happy for the raiders, from reading so far sounds like high-end raid guilds got everything that they wanted. I sure hope those raid guilds can support SOE on their own.<br />
<br />
Saar</p>
	
	
	
	
