	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Binter</b><br /><i>Welcome to EverRaid.<br />
<br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>So tell me, are the raiders the ones generating the lion's share of the EQ revenue?  I seriously doubt it.  Sounds like the casual players are the heart of the player base, which again is being ignored.  I knew this would happen when I saw who they were inviting to this summit.  Fine, if they want to focus on high end raiding, then they can watch their player base shrink to a few thousand while CoH and WoW get their player bases to 500k+, because they cater to casual players first, not just power players.  They've got the 80/20 rule backwards and continue to focus on the 20%, what morons.<br />
<br />
I guess no mention of fixing the quad zillion bugs currently in the game, except those that affect raiders.  What a bunch of crap.  I've already canceled my account and will not be reactivating.  2hb will still be broken, etc., etc.  Screw the Plane of Time, I'll never see it (and neither will most players, don't they realize this?).  By God, we all pay the same monthly fee.  <br />
<br />
The only items that even remotely interest me are the LDoN changes to augments (more of a fix than an enhancement, come on, an augment has to be detroyed to change it, stupid idea from the start) and the single player LDoN missions.  Once again they are copying another game, in this case CoH.  Unfortunately, where as CoH was developed with this concept in mind EQ was not.  It will take SoE months to come up with a way to allow all classes to complete solo LDoN missions and balance the challenge and reward appropriately.  I'm not holding my breath, or willing to wait that long.  <br />
<br />
SoE will never see my $12.95 again.<br />
<br />
Thunderwolf</p>
	
	
	
	
