<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Juujuu</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Oracle<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 1999<br />
	Location: Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Approximately 5000 points per item (item plus augs)<br />
Approximately 100 adventures per item (51 points per adventure)<br />
Approximately 150-200 hours per item (1.5-2 hours per adventure)<br />
Multiply that by 10 items<br />
1500-2000 HOURS or LDoN time for those items<br />
Divide by 20 hours per week<br />
75-100 WEEKS<br />
Divide by 52 (weeks in a year)<br />
<br />
Final:<br />
1.5 - 2 YEARS of time for 10 pieces of gear.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Shaman armor costs 1500 points a slot.<br />
Type 2 augments, and type 3 augments only cost 1100.<br />
Spending 600 points for an 8 stat augment for 2 stats, or a 5ac augment isn't really worth it for the type 1 slot, especially when you can loot free 6stat/resist augments doing your adventures.<br />
Each piece in reality costs 3700 points.<br />
<br />
1.5 hours for 51 points.<br />
72 adventures will pay for it.<br />
That's 110 hours to get a piece of top of the line gear from ldon.<br />
18 equipment slots needing gear averages out to 2000 hours of ldon.<br />
Keep in mind you also get xp and AAs doing this, and your charm augment will be maxed out in stats because of it.<br />
<br />
Raiding:<br />
My guild uses a database to keep track of our raiding hours and loot.<br />
Since December 5th, 2002, I've won 29 items raiding with my guild.<br />
That's 18th months worth of raiding almost to the day.<br />
I've contributed 590 hours raiding with my guild (not including travel time to wherever we are raiding).<br />
The items I've won range from mostly VT and Ssra gear at first (10+ pieces) to a few ele plane items (about 8) to a few pieces of Time gear at the end.<br />
On average it takes me about 20 hours of time to get a new piece of gear.<br />
I also receive no xp during any of that.  My AA meter goes up a bit, but my normal xp meterd drops due to dying often multiple times on a raid.<br />
<br />
For ldon, it's about 5.5 times longer to get VT and Ele plane quality gear, and as an added reward your charm augment maxes out and you get a huge number of AAs.<br />
For raiding, you get no xp for doing so, but the items on average need less time to acquire.  Also, you have to factor in such things as difficulty in figuring out how to actually kill certain raid targets, and spend hours upon hours doing so (Xegony corpse coh + kill usually takes about 4 hours for us in total.  The entire coh + Rathe council kill took us 6 full hours last time we did it with "just" 55 people on the raid).<br />
With ldon, you aren't locked into being there for anything longer than 2.0 including CR, *ever*.<br />
<br />
There's a balance between the 2 of them.  Raiding is faster gear, but you don't get xp.  LDON is xp, but you get gear slower.  I don't xp much due to work/sleep/social life/raiding, but I do xp here and there regardless, and getting an item out of doing what I'm already doing anywhere rocks.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Juujuu Bigmojo<br />
65 Human Shaman<br />
Brell Server<br />
Watchers</div>
	
	
