	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I've got 2 things in this thread I'd like to address...<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Like how often in the last month have you grouped with a tank and cleric not from your guild? People that have less than 100 AAs? A tank with less than 6000 hps unbuffed?<hr size="1" /></blockquote>I know I wasn't the target of this, but since I've been posting a lot recently, I figure I'll chime in with my credentials.  <br />
<br />
I frequently group outside my guild, almost daily in fact.  I don't care what the guild tag is, I group friends first, players I know to be competant and friendly second, random guildmembers and evals that I don't know well third, random people who I'll give a chance fourth, and known incompetant or obnoxious players not at all.<br />
<br />
I'm grouped with people with less than 100 AA more often than not.  The player I spend the most time with currently has 31 AA as I post this.<br />
<br />
I frequently do content with no tank other than a 63 ranger with 3600 unbuffed hp.  This includes Riwwi, Barindu, Ferubi, and Vxed.  Admittedly, we don't do Vxed without an enchanter charm pet when we have no better tank than that ranger ... but we've 4-manned Umbiki this way (last character was a cleric with something like a 3k mana pool, so it wasn't uber either).<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />1.5 hours for 51 points.<br />
72 adventures will pay for it.<br />
That's 110 hours to get a piece of top of the line gear from ldon.<br />
18 equipment slots needing gear averages out to 2000 hours of ldon.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Filling all 18 slots with LDoN point-buy gear is insane.  There are a handful of choice LDoN pieces, but much of it is chaff.  Even ignoring GoD for a moment, the Bazaar even provides upgrades to several of the LDoN point buy items.  One bracer can be a Stone Bracer of Battle Mastery.  Boots of an Aged Mystic are amazingly better than Incorporeal.  I'd take a Vampiric Coif of the Grave, as well.  Sure, its not cheap, but LDoN isn't terrible cash, either, especially Miragul.  By the time you have a couple of fully aug'ed LDoN pieces, you'll have the money to pick up one of the other items in the bazaar.  If you have a group of friends who'll do hard LDoN for loot (you don't even have to win - just have a tracker and farm, who cares about the stupid leaderboard?  you're casual, right?), then you can probably pick those 3 items up for free eventually, and get several other amazing items, like the Girdle of Bloodstained Stones, the Spectral Earring of Froglok Essence, and the FT2 cloak whose name escapes me totally at the moment.  I wouldn't think that anyone looking to gear well, with forward planning, would WANT more than about 6 fully aug'ed LDoN point buy items, at the outside.  The more GoD-ambitious plans my friends have crafted include only 2-4 pieces each.<br />
<br />
Of course, everything does need a (generally 1150 pt) aug, which takes about 35 hours to acquire.  So ... the total time to acquire 4 key peices of LDoN gear and to completely augment everything else is:<br />
<br />
(110 * 4) + (35 * [18 - 4]) = 930 hours.  <br />
<br />
Of course, I wouldn't go that far, anyway.  You don't really need to stick the 20/20 augments in *everything* they can go in.  They're good, sure, but not earth-shatteringly good.  And by the time you're halfway done with this, a group of similar equipped people ought to be able to pick up the 2 25/25 augs in Ferubi, and (depending on available classes), quite likely could get the 30/30 and 30 hp augs from the front of Tipt, too.  That's not counting any other augs you get, like the 20 hp ones in Natimbi, or the various focus augments from the sewers.<br />
<br />
LDoN *is* good ... in moderation.  Remember that there's other content too. =)</p>
	
	
	
	
	
