	<p><i>-potime fixes (not true instancing yet but a step -- i was told full instancing will take a bit longer due to having to make major changes)</i><br />
Soooo very needed.  Full instancing ala LDON and GoD is what's really needed, but nixing the 4 hour wait for an empty Time instance to expire will be nice.  We have a guild on Brell that raids fairly late in the day (PST based), while my guild and a soon to be time flagged guild are running on EST time.  We can't raid the same day, because the moment our p1-4 raid hits phase 5, our instance won't expire for another 5 or 6 hours.  Being able to clear phase 5, but leave phase 5 and quarm for another day, and let someone else with a later time zone take over the zone for the next few hours will cause much less headache for picking days of the week you can raid time.  We only have 4 guilds on Brell that raid time, and already the days of the week are getting cramped for whose raiding what days.  Adding more guilds will just make it messier.<br />
<br />
<i>-raid message of the day (?***)</i><br />
Eh.  Don't really need it.  That's what /guildmotd is for.<br />
<br />
<i>-improving how soe handles beta and the testing process</i><br />
About freaking time.  God should still be in testing to this day.  Can't say enough about this, but everyone already knows how bad their testing and patch process is.  If they would just put their patches on the *test server* for a week before pushing it out the door, or hell, even a day or 2, it would fix sooooo much complaining from the player base.<br />
<br />
<i>-increasing the number of debuffs allowed on a mob</i><br />
And the necros rejoice!  This was really needed.  malosinia, DR debuff, ro, mark, mark, cripple, slow, hos, tash take up a quick 9 slots.  The remaining 21 slots must be shared by the 50-70 other people on the raid.  Many raiders have weapons that proc dots or other debuffs.  A single necro can quite easily stack 4-5 dots on a mob.  Stick 4 necros on a mob, and your debuff limit is full.<br />
<br />
<i>-increase buffslots on players through aa</i><br />
Wooo.  This is sorely needed.  What buffs do I have up about 90% of the time doing xp and raiding?  Clarity, fos, 9, symbol, AC, regen, sow, horse, haste, JBB right clicky, BST clarity, BSS, right clicky quarm ring.  This is before I even think about getting any types of resist or ranger buffs or damage sheilds.<br />
<br />
<i>-note field on the raid window</i><br />
Don't see a need for this.<br />
<br />
<i>-improved consent (/consent guild) and drag. /consent raid, guild, or group.<br />
-improve corpse drag radius</i><br />
And the rogues of the world rejoice!  This is so so needed.  You don't have to hear rogues scream after every wipe to mass consent them, and have afk people not do consents and demand their resses and take up huge amounts of time.  If I can autoconsent my guild upon a death, that would be heaven.<br />
When playing my own characters, if I have spirit of wolf up, I can't drag corpses, because they get left behind after dx9.  The corpses don't update position fast enough so I have to either drop sow or duck so I move slow enough for corpses to keep up.<br />
<br />
<br />
<i>-make charms not no drop</i><br />
Nice change.  Not a really big deal since the POP charm is free at level 51 and the only one most people I know would bother to equip, but *shrug*<br />
<br />
<br />
The "longer to-do list" - again, not everything but this is what they'll be discussing immediately:<br />
<br />
<i>-back flagging solutions</i><br />
Very late in being discussed, but with the continuing need for backflagging now with GoD, as well as POP, this is wonderful.  Hopefully they can do something like give a guild a free "tradable" flag  or something if you can just get a sizable enough portion of already flagged people into the zone.  For example, if MM is up, and you have 95% of your raid of 50+ people flagged for the zone, and already have MM flag, then you could flag the remaining 5% of the people without going through the whole raid.  Limit how often you can do this to something like once per week or once per month.  You don't need Time raiding guilds ganking MM from lower tier guilds killing him for flags and loot.<br />
<br />
<i>-improved raid and guild functionality</i><br />
interesting to see what they might change<br />
<br />
<i>-auto loot for your corpse</i><br />
Awesome.  About time.  About 5 years late, but better late than never.<br />
<br />
<i>-improvements to raid xp</i><br />
Nice.  Not really necessary, but would be cool to see.<br />
<br />
<i>-no more alien NPC's (focussing more on familiar norrathian themes)</i><br />
Yay.  **** hynid.  **** mastruqs.  **** aneuks.  **** all those wierd mobs.  Gimme dragons and kobolds and goblins and golems and giant spiders and elementals and stuff.<br />
<br />
<i>-solo ldon-stle instanced or similar content</i><br />
Weeee.  I've wanted to solo an ldon adventure for so long, but the time requirements, and 3 person group requirements restrict it.  Much joy.<br />
<br />
<i>-issues with item augmentations (also refers to focii/effects i believe)-augments will be removeable quite soon.<br />
</i><br />
More types of focus augments would rock.  More slots for focus augments would rock.  Being able to retrieve an augment from a slot is vastly needed.  Selling back old armor for a fraction of points spent would rock.  Much potential here.<br />
<br />
<i>-possible enhancements to /guildwar</i><br />
Never been in a guildwar, but wouldn't mind it some time.<br />
<br />
<i>- Probably going to be a way to see the time left on your buffs soon.</i><br />
Excellent.  About freaking time.<br />
<br />
<i>-there is new armors coming to ldon, and the 1452 or whatever the cap is now will be raised.</i><br />
Neat.  Now maybe people in Elemental/VT armor will get something out of the expansion besides just boring 40hp augments.<br />
<br />
<br />
<i>-spell drops in god are being changed somewhat. Also quests to get some of the spells.</i><br />
About freaking time.  I've seen about 6 spells drop so far ever, and they were all on an ikkinz raid (rune type turn in).  I've only managed to acquire my slow because someone else in my guild xping in kod'taz got it and I was in the area at the time to run over and loot.  I've been hunting in god a LOT due to BIC quest, and ever since the expansion went live, I've only known about 10 poeple to get any spells at all in the *entire expansion*.  That's lame.<br />
<br />
<br />
<i>-vp revamp coming very soon.</i><br />
Interesting.  The old zone was very cool.  I wish I could get more friends to go there.<br />
<br />
<i>-Much much much better CS is coming soon. Their csr tools they have available now are simply amazing. If you'd given up petitioning about problems, you should start again.</i><br />
I had someone harrassing me the other day.  He was spamming me with rude tells, spamming me with group invites, and standing in my face no matter where I faced because I didn't want to do a sewers group with him.  He started logging to other characters to chase me when I gated to PoK.  I sent in a petition (after having to ask a guide how to even send in a petition now).  It took a full 30+ hours for a GM to put an update in my ticket saying "we'll look into it".  *joy*.  Thanks for the prompt service jackass.</p>
	
	
	
