	<!-- message -->
	<p>Oh, I personally think there are many many options to just going through LDON to equip all 20 equipment slots.  But just to put the time investment into perspective, I assumed all slots were filled by LDON stuff.<br />
<br />
In real practice, there's much better things to do for loot and xp and augments.  Every successful run through Tipt will net you an item off the final boss (either a bracer or ****ty charm thing), and an augment of some kind.  If you want, you can just zone in, kill the cragbeast boss for the augment, and leave to redo.  Spend an hour with a group, and someone gets a new FT2 augment, 30hp/mana augment, or 2hp regen +10 attack augment, or whatever the other one is.  Take a group to Ferubi, crawl the zone to the named that drop parts for Rondo, and farm them for augments.  Take a group into sewers, do xp in there and get item drops off the named that will pop.  You can get a 90hp fungal tunic by xping anywhere in Riwwi, as well as see the occasional named mob.  A single group can flag themselves for Kod'Taz without a raid, and obtain loot there that's Plane of Time quality, obtainable by a single xp group.<br />
<br />
LDON are good for filling in slots that you haven't seen good upgrades for.  Besides 150k cost ornate legs, or farwater legs, you won't find many good legs for a shaman, so might as well get some good LDON legs out of there.  A good bracer is easy to acquire from Tipt boss, or just buying relatively cheap ornate for the FT2, so you might want to skip the LDON armor for that slot.</p>
	
	
	
