	Joined: Mar 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I have mixed feelings about LDoN legs post-GoD.  On one hand, they are very likely most people's bad slot.  Past Tae Ew, and assuming no ornate, you have ... well, yeah, okay, that WAS a short list.  Elemental crafted (Livestone, Farwater, etc.) tends to be expensive enough to be out of reach if you aren't already able to buy Ornate anyway.  Stuff like Veteran's Chain Leggings are a pretty marginal improvement.<br />
<br />
But, then again, if you're at the point where you can farm Vxed, the Seamless Spiked Leggings are a better choice.<br />
<br />
I tend to feel that the best slots for LDoN gear for shaman are the BP (Ornate is just too pricey, and although the clicky is *useful* its not in the same category as an actual focus effect), and gloves (since good gloves are just non-existant in this game, it seems).  If you can manage to find IH4 somewhere else (perhaps by putting a Rathe totem in ranged, or even in secondary if you get the Ferubi totem for ranged MP4), then arms are another good LDoN candidate.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
