<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Benadan</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Dec 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Saar_Tribunal</b><br /><i>I dont get why raiders especially serious raiders seem to think LDoN is a panacea for the non-raider.<br />
<br />
Completely over looking the repetitiveness of it, the blandness, etc lets look at time investment.<br />
<br />
Approximately 5000 points per item (item plus augs)<br />
Approximately 100 adventures per item (51 points per adventure)<br />
Approximately 150-200 hours per item (1.5-2 hours per adventure)<br />
Multiply that by 10 items<br />
1500-2000 HOURS or LDoN time for those items<br />
Divide by 20 hours per week<br />
75-100 WEEKS<br />
Divide by 52 (weeks in a year)<br />
<br />
Final:<br />
1.5 - 2 YEARS of time for 10 pieces of gear.<br />
<br />
<br />
Saar</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>1.5 - 2 hours per adventure? Something is seriously wrong there. I am Bazaar geared and finish a normal LDoN in 30 to 45 minutes. It takes something seriously going wrong for it to take longer than that. A hard LDoN can take as much as the full time alotment, but its not worth it. In the time it takes to do a single 70 point adventure, I can do 2 - 51 point adventures, and make more points.<br />
<br />
At 51 points per adventure you are looking at 98 adventures (4998 points) not 100. <br />
98 * 45 minutes =  73.5 hours<br />
By your 10 items is 735 hours<br />
Dividing by 20 hours a week is 36.75 weeks<br />
Figuring a month as 4 weeks that in just over 9 months.<br />
<br />
I am using your numbers here to make the points that a) it should not take that long to get the gear, and b) there are issues in the way the groups you have been in are working together. I would suggest that you look at the group dynamics and see what could be done to improve them. <br />
B) is not intended as a flame in any way. I am not going to guess at what the problem is, but something is not clicking for your groups.<br />
<br />
As for Augs (based on <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?threadid=17949" target="_blank">Quick Purchasable Augment List </a> <br />
1450 pnts - 5 augs<br />
1150 pnts - 9 augs<br />
760 pnts - 7 augs<br />
510 pnts - 3 augs<br />
340 pnts - 3 augs<br />
150, 100, and 40 pnts - 1 aug at each level.<br />
That makes the average aug price 859 points.<br />
Based on the average aug price and a piece of 1492 armor that places the completed slot at 4069 points not 5000.<br />
That is 80 adventures with points left over.<br />
End result of this is 7 and a half months to equip 10 slots.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
