	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Thunderwolfjr</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Teacher<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: May 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I agree, this one is the only really significant change which would benefit the casual and raid players alike.   However, don't hold your breath waiting or it.  This will be incredibly hard for SoE to implement for all classes at all levels with the appropriate level of risk/reward.  If they give melee classes NPC healers, why wouldn't they give casters NPC kei?, etc., etc.  City of Heroes can do this, and does it well, because it was designed around this concept.  Trying to bandaid EQ at this point will be next to impossible.  <br />
<br />
Don't get me wrong, I'd love to see this go live, I just don't have the faith in SoE.  This was low on their list and the amount of effort to make it work is huge.  I just don't see them making the investment with Omens a few weeks away and EQII by year end.  <br />
<br />
This summit and it's results/promises offer absolutely nothing to the casual gamer. Raiders rejoice, you will soon have the servers to yourselves.  The 30-50 crowd, as they stated, will be gone, due to neglect.<br />
<br />
Thunderwolf</p>
	
	
	
	
	
